== Garlic Rice ==

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium heat with the
@oil{1/2%tbsp}. Once hot, add half the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%grams} until coated, ~{1%minute}. Add
@salt{1/4%tsp} and the @water{300%ml} for the rice and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Salmon ==

Meanwhile, lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined
#baking tray{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then rub to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through,
~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked
> when opaque in the middle.

== Soy Fried Veg ==

While the salmon roasts, heat a drizzle of @oil{1/2%tbsp} in a large
#frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @mangetout{80%grams} and @sliced mushrooms{80%grams} to the
pan and stir-fry until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the remaining garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @soy sauce{15%ml} until evaporated, ~{1%minute}. Transfer the
cooked veg to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Hot Honey Sauce ==

When everything's nearly ready, clean out the (now empty) frying pan and pop
back on medium heat.

Add the @hot sauce{50%grams}, @honey{15%grams}, @butter{30%grams} and @water{2%tbsp}
for the sauce and stir vigorously until the butter has melted and the sauce
is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for
> ~{1%minute} to loosen.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the garlic rice with a #fork{} and share between your serving bowls.

Top with the salmon and soy stir-fried veg. Spoon the hot honey sauce over the
salmon fillets.

Drizzle over the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} to finish.

Enjoy!